EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO HEALTH AND SAFETY -- OFFICE OF STATE FIRE MARSHAL
***
1 This act would create a voluntary program through which registrants of electric and hybrid
2 motor vehicles can request stickers to affix to enclosures housing such vehicles to promote first
3 responders' safety in relation to electrical fires. The act would also require that the division of motor
4 vehicles maintain a list of electric and hybrid motor vehicle registrations and send quarterly lists of
5 such registrations to the fire departments and fire districts within the state.
6 This act would take effect on January 1, 2026.
